Co-expression networks

Erica Padial Fuillerat

27/7/2020

First co-expression network:

Loading the already processed expression data:

library(CoExpNets)
library(CoExpROSMAP)
## 
## Attaching package: 'CoExpROSMAP'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:CoExpNets':
## 
##     getCovariates, initDb
library(WGCNA)
## Loading required package: dynamicTreeCut
## Loading required package: fastcluster
## 
## Attaching package: 'fastcluster'
## The following object is masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     hclust
## 
## 
## Attaching package: 'WGCNA'
## The following object is masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     cor
enableWGCNAThreads(10)
## Allowing parallel execution with up to 10 working processes.
genes.para.red <- readRDS("/media/erica/ERIKA/copia/MASTER/Segundo_cuatrimestre/TFM/RDSs_procesamiento_datos_expresion/genes_para_red.rds")

Launch of the network for such expression data:

net = CoExpNets::getDownstreamNetwork(
        n.iterations=50,
        net.type = "signed",
        debug=F,
        fullAnnotation = T,
        expr.data=genes.para.red,
        save.plots=T,
        job.path="/media/erica/ERIKA/copia/MASTER/Segundo_cuatrimestre/TFM/Red1")

We load the network and sort its modules:

net.name="/media/erica/ERIKA/copia/MASTER/Segundo_cuatrimestre/TFM/Red1/netmytissue.6.it.50.rds"
net1=readRDS(net.name)
sort(table(net1$moduleColors),decreasing=T)
## 
##     black     green     brown turquoise      blue    yellow       red 
##      8195      3709      1379      1270      1199      1130       912

Loading of the already processed patients clinical data:

datos_pacientes=readRDS("/media/erica/ERIKA/copia/MASTER/Segundo_cuatrimestre/TFM/RDS_procesamiento_datos_clinicos/datos_pacientes.rds")

Joining the patients identifiers with the corresponding ages:

library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
pacientes.por.edad <- datos_pacientes[with(datos_pacientes, order(datos_pacientes$BiobankCode)), ]  #We sort data frame "datos _pacientes" by column "biobankCode", in order to have patients at the same order than data frame "genes.para.red".
pacientes.por.edad <- pacientes.por.edad[-(c(13,21,78)),] #Erasing the three patients whose expression data were degraded.
pacientes_edad <- data.frame(rownames(genes.para.red),pacientes.por.edad$age,row.names = 1) #Creation of a new data frame formed by patients used in the network and their corresponding age.
pacientes_edad <- rename(pacientes_edad, age = pacientes.por.edad.age)  #Rename variable age.

Correlation analysis of the first co-expression network:

We study the correlation between network data and “age” covariate:

corWithNumTraits(which.one = "new", tissue = net1, covlist = colnames(pacientes_edad), covs = pacientes_edad)

Since there is a correlation with age, we are going to eliminate this correlation from data in order to obtain residuals of free data from it:

genes.para.red.t <- data.frame(t(genes.para.red)) #Putting patients as columns and genes as rows again.
print("Getting residuals")
## [1] "Getting residuals"
residuos.sin.edad <- apply(genes.para.red.t, 1, function(y){  #Apply function "y" to each row of data frame "genes.para.red.t". That function makes a linear regression (function "lm") regarding to residuals from data frame "pacientes_edad", where is the co-variable whose correlation (age) we want to eliminate.
  lm( y ~ . , data=cbind(pacientes_edad))$residuals
})

Second Coexpression Network:

Generation of the network again, this time with new residuals that must not correlate with age:

net = CoExpNets::getDownstreamNetwork(
        n.iterations=50,
        net.type = "signed",
        debug=F,
        fullAnnotation = T,
        expr.data=residuos.sin.edad,
        save.plots=T,
        job.path="/media/erica/ERIKA/copia/MASTER/Segundo_cuatrimestre/TFM/Red2")
net.name2="/media/erica/ERIKA/copia/MASTER/Segundo_cuatrimestre/TFM/Red2/netmytissue.6.it.50.rds"
net2=readRDS(net.name2)
sort(table(net2$moduleColors),decreasing=T)

Correlation analysis of the second co-expression network:

We calculate the correlation to confirm it has been removed:

corWithNumTraits(which.one = "new", tissue = net2, covlist = colnames(pacientes_edad), covs = pacientes_edad)

Selecting in a new data frame the rest of covariables we are interested in analyzing their correlation with genes:

covs_pacientes <- data.frame(rownames(genes.para.red),pacientes.por.edad[,4:129],row.names = 1) #Select covariables of "pacientes.por.edad" which already were sorted by patient.
covs_pacientes <- covs_pacientes[,-c(7,9,10,16,51,52,53,54,55,56,57,58,89,121,126)] #We erase those covariables corresponding to dates.

Analyze this correlation:
